<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>She hosts one of Melbourne's most popular FM breakfast shows.</p>

<p>And on Wednesday, Chrissie Swan stepped out for a much needed caffeine fix in Melbourne.</p>

<p>The 46-year-old radio host was spotted picking up takeaway coffees in a leopard-print face mask amid the city's stage four lockdown restrictions.</p>

<p>Coffee run: Chrissie Swan stepped out for a caffeine fix in Melbourne on Wednesday</p>

<p>She wore a Mickey Mouse grey sweater which she paired with black exercise leggings and matching sneakers.</p>

<p>The Australian television presenter appeared to have gone makeup-free for the outing.</p>

<p>She kept her long brunette locked pushed back behind her hair with a pair of designer sunglasses.</p>

<p>Low-key: She wore a Mickey Mouse sweater grey sweater which she paired with black exercise leggings and matching sneakers</p>

<p>After parking her brown SUV on the street, Chrissie emerged from the vehicle and made her way into a nearby cafe.</p>

<p>It was a brief outing for the media personality, who then climbed back into her car and returned home.</p>

<p>The appearance comes just two days after Chrissie encouraged fellow Melburnians that they are 'almost there' on Instagram.</p>

